=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_FFT-Overview_ex5 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral gritty sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 713 Hz, featuring instant attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is early, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: early

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 712.7190
  harmonic_decay_rate: -2.6350
  harmonic_regularity: 0.4861
  pitch_clarity: 27.0382
  inharmonicity: 0.1779
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.3624
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FFT Overview Example 5
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/FFT-Overview.html
// Tags: FFT-Overview, Guides, spectral
// ---
// --- Example 5 ---
(
{
  var in, chain;
    in = Ringz.ar(Impulse.ar([2, 3]), [700, 800], 0.1) * 5; // stereo input
    chain = FFT({ LocalBuf(2048) } ! 2, in); // array of two local buffers
    chain = PV_RandComb(chain, 0.95, Impulse.kr(0.4));
    IFFT(chain) // returns a stereo out
}.play;
)
